   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">First off I don&#39;t want this deck rated bad because i put it in advanced and not fun.  It is a really good deck that keeps your opponent at bay.  I am going to put it in as a fun deck as well.<br>
<br>
Mobis:  Mobis is their to try and take out atleast one magi.  He will come into play, play bwill and wellisk and if i get any other creatures (besides and hyren) I will play them.  That is for if i go first.  If i go second I will first use a discard spell that I pull off the the top 3 cards.  I usually get a discard spell or maelstrom flask.  So I will try to use a discard spell and then play my creatures.<br>
<br>
Trug:  Everyone knows what Trug is thier for.  I just flip him and pop him.  I used to run Voda up front but... I didn&#39;t have any of his starting cards in the deck and it was pretty hard to keep him in play because how the deck as mainly all small creatures.<br>
<br>
Quilla:  She just whoops ass.  I most always grab a spear and bubble with her.  Her high energize rate allows me to unleash total madness when she flips.  I have enough energy to do a double tidal wave and still have one energy.<br>
<br>
Combos:  Using the goggles and maelstrom flask and orthean horn.<br>
<br>
Orwins gaze and Orthean Horn or Maelstrom Flask.<br>
<br>
Mobis and Trug (The main combo of the deck :)....)<br>
<br>
Well please rate this deck accordingly and let me know your opinions. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
